At Frank's Fruit Market, 3 bananas cost as much as 2 apples, and 6 apples cost as much as 4 oranges. How many oranges cost as much as 18 bananas?

}

\textbf{Answer:} Because 3 bananas cost as much as 2 apples, 18 bananas cost as much as 12 apples. Because 6 apples cost as much as 4 oranges, 12 apples cost as much as 8 oranges. Therefore 18 bananas cost as much as $\boxed{8}$ oranges.
